trend_summary: Built-up areas creep outward from the highway corridor and coastal node, filling gaps but staying compact. Quarry pits enlarge mid-period, then show partial revegetation. Southern wetland margins fluctuate, with later images displaying more open water. Forest cover is largely retained, so growth is steady rather than explosive, keeping an overall suburban, medium-density character.
notable_changes: Incremental residential and industrial infill along the central highway spine.
New blocks added near the northern coastal settlement.
Quarry/extraction zones expand between middle years, then start to green over.
Wetland or lagoon in the south shows higher water coverage in later imagery.
Minor road network extensions and junction upgrades observed.
